This leads to a dual-purpose outcome: not only do we develop more potent adversarial attacks, but we also generate diagnostic tools for stress-testing model robustness. The insights could directly inform *adversarial training pipelines* that specifically harden models against grammar-preserving, semantically coherent evasion tactics.

